	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Heh, "accurate speed" is a very interesting term! But I guess you are right, the closer to 60 fps, the more accurate the speed is.
<br />
<br />When developing I try to get the I/O stuff out of the way first, and this is when emulator accuracy is most important. However, it has happened to me before that something that *shouldn't* be directly related to I/O broke some of the I/O logic. So I use Nintendulator and Nestopia during all my programming sessions, and every few days I test it on the PowerPak as well (even multiples times in a day if I'm doing something too hardcore that looks funky on emulators).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
